evaluation.response:
Conversations around needs as you now see them can go far to change the direction of these talks.

Why not ask her to give you breakdown on reasons you need to move to memory care? Maybe there's some things you can work on to control these so-called “Symptoms”. She may be anxious not to have to put you in a home. Depending upon the way your living situation is impacted by your request she also may understand everything that you say too.

While it is normal to face the test of having caring family and friends giving confusing messages in this uncommon situation mostly if they are waiting for some signs of disease, relying upon everyone to assist you both day and night to keep everything under control certainly isn’t abnormal.&#x20;
